dc_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Lauenburg, sheet J-12. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Lauenburg, Lithuania. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 and Nord de guerre zone grids. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Germany 1:25,000. German General Staff 1877-1933; Germany, 1:100,000, German General Staff, sheet 12, 1927; Poland, 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, Sheets 29-26, 1935; 30-26, 1937; 31-25, 1937 and 31-26, 1937. Road classification in Poland based on British intelligence reports. Map states location as Germany though the map actually depicts Poland.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
